seagrass_notes: The larger Richardson Bay eelgrass bed is dynamic and variable in size, approximately 100-300 hectares (~300 in 2019). The area we sampled was a largely continuous portion of the bed. Eelgrass is patchy - approximately 1 m diameter patches 1-5 m apart. Density approx. 25-30 shoots/m^2 (max density 68 shoots/m^2), canopy height approx. 150 cm.
describe_transect: sampling transect along a NW line parallel to the Sausalito shoreline, 10 m apart, consistent depth of water (1-1.25 m) and sample (~ 30 cm below the surface). Sampled taken towards shore due to wind from the W and ebb tide (so current was moving from pole sampler to the person, to minimize contamination from the wetsuit).
notes: Wildlife observations: brown pelican, harbor seal.  Phyllaplysia taylori seen on seagrass
